"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\nRabbi Dr. Asher Meir, Business Ethics Center of Jerusalem  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.aish.com/societyWork/work/The_Jewish_Ethicist__-_Devious_Discount1.asp\">\"Discounted from what?\" </a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Marketing and Morality - Breaking the Barrier\" <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jabe.org/marketing-and-morality-breaking-the-barrier.html\">Jewish Association of Business Ethics</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080705083713/http://www.jabe.org/marketing-and-morality-breaking-the-barrier.html\">Archived</a> 2008-07-05 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>. Retrieved 2-21-08.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Tamari, Meir. <i>Al Chet: Sins in the Marketplace</i>, 1996 Rowman &amp; Littlefield <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-56821-906-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-56821-906-7\">1-56821-906-7</a> pp.73ff.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Advertising\" <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jabe.org/advertising.html\">Jewish Association of Business Ethics</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080705083321/http://www.jabe.org/advertising.html\">Archived</a> 2008-07-05 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>. Retrieved 2-21-08.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Levine 2000, p.198.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Mark Warshofsky p.308 <i>Jewish Living: A Guide to Contemporary Reform Practice</i>  2000 <a href=\"/wiki/Union_for_Reform_Judaism\" title=\"Union for Reform Judaism\">Union for Reform Judaism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8074-0702-X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8074-0702-X\">0-8074-0702-X</a>. He's referring (per p466) to Walter Jacob, <i>Question and Reform Jewish Answers</i>, #91</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Feinstein, Moshe. <i>Igrot Moshe</i> HM 2:29-30.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-14\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Levine, Aaron. \"Using Secondary Sources Without Attribution\" in <i>Moral Issues of the Marketplace in Jewish Law</i>, Yashar Books, 2005. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-933143-09-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-933143-09-6\">1-933143-09-6</a>, pp. 31-35</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Halakha_(Jewish_religious_law)\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Ha